<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="495" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/779.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Smith</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The President abdicated at three o’clock and has gone on board German war
                            vessel <hi rend="italic">Vineta</hi>. There was much firing and disorder
                            but the city is in charge of civil authorities who assume all
                            responsibility. <hi rend="italic">Montana</hi> is preparing to land
                            twenty-seven men as Legation guard. <hi rend="italic">Vineta</hi> will
                            do likewise. Revolutionists have not yet entered city but are reported
                            on the way from St. Marco.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>